MATCH_TOOL: Bash
MATCH_PATTERN: git mv .+ _legacy|mkdir.+_legacy|mv .+ _legacy
ADVISORY: |
  When parking orphaned code under a `_legacy/` folder as a safety net (instead
  of deleting outright), its relative imports go stale because the path depth
  changed. `tsc --noEmit` will then fail with "Cannot find module ../..." errors
  on every file you moved — even though nothing in the live tree imports them.

  Fix: add `"exclude": ["src/shells/<shell>/_legacy"]` (or equivalent path) to
  the relevant `tsconfig.json` in the SAME commit. This keeps the parked code
  on disk as a reference without polluting the type-check surface.

  Wrong (commits but `npm run build` fails):
    git mv components/TabBar.tsx _legacy/TabBar.tsx
    git commit -m "chore: park legacy"
    # next command: npx tsc --noEmit → dozens of TS2307 errors

  Right (commit the exclude together):
    git mv components/TabBar.tsx _legacy/TabBar.tsx
    # edit tsconfig.json: add _legacy to exclude
    git add tsconfig.json
    git commit -m "chore: park legacy under _legacy/ + exclude from tsc"

  This is a procedural companion to the general "keep work in _legacy/ until
  playtest passes" pattern — the exclude is non-obvious but non-negotiable.
